full_text: @elliejoypanic Every bit of talk about mental health and talking about your own experiences helps, and it's very important to talk about mental health not just today, but everytime. Thanks for doing that.
full_text(utf-8): b"@elliejoypanic Every bit of talk about mental health and talking about your own experiences helps, and it's very important to talk about mental health not just today, but everytime. Thanks for doing that."

full_text:
You are not broken because you have mental health issues. Seek professional help. I know it's easy to say these things. I struggled with following that advice as well.
Seeking help is NEVER a sign of weakness. It is ALWAYS a sign of strength. Have a wonderful day. Take care.
full_text(utf-8): b"You are not broken because you have mental health issues. Seek professional help. I know it's easy to say these things. I struggled with following that advice as well.\nSeeking help is NEVER a sign of weakness. It is ALWAYS a sign of strength. Have a wonderful day. Take care."

full_text: There are a few things I want you to take away from this if you struggle with depression, or even more if you are not yet in professional care but suspect that something might be there. You are not alone. Talk to your friends and other people close to you.
full_text(utf-8): b'There are a few things I want you to take away from this if you struggle with depression, or even more if you are not yet in professional care but suspect that something might be there. You are not alone. Talk to your friends and other people close to you.'

full_text: Those issues don't just go away - you learn how to spot them earlier, how to react. And you learn to ask for help. I learned to be more open, and to communicate better. I have to fight my old urges of running away, but most of the time I do it successfully.
full_text(utf-8): b"Those issues don't just go away - you learn how to spot them earlier, how to react. And you learn to ask for help. I learned to be more open, and to communicate better. I have to fight my old urges of running away, but most of the time I do it successfully."

full_text:
I learned that my catatonic phases we're not laziness, but a reaction to having too much on my shoulders.

I had therapy for two years, but it took long until I really could use what I learned in everytime life. I still struggle sometimes.
full_text(utf-8): b"I learned that my catatonic phases we're not laziness, but a reaction to having too much on my shoulders.\n\nI had therapy for two years, but it took long until I really could use what I learned in everytime life. I still struggle sometimes."

full_text: But in therapy I learned of the toxic ways I "handled" conflicts, and I learned to accept myself more. I learned that it is ok to say "it's too much for me" and "I need to slow down", without just stopping.
full_text(utf-8): b'But in therapy I learned of the toxic ways I "handled" conflicts, and I learned to accept myself more. I learned that it is ok to say "it\'s too much for me" and "I need to slow down", without just stopping.'

full_text:
I had a tendency to lie, I wanted to avoid conflict at all cost, and I often fell into phases of almost catatonic disinterest in anything. 
I had therapy to work on my issues, but my doctor did not prescibe antidepressives - something that I now think was a mistake.
full_text(utf-8): b'I had a tendency to lie, I wanted to avoid conflict at all cost, and I often fell into phases of almost catatonic disinterest in anything. \nI had therapy to work on my issues, but my doctor did not prescibe antidepressives - something that I now think was a mistake.'

full_text: In 2017 I was diagnosed with depression and anxiety disorder. As many people I was hesitant to accept that, and accept help. I thought I was just overworked or exhausted. But I came to realize that fear was at the core of who I was and what I did.
full_text(utf-8): b'In 2017 I was diagnosed with depression and anxiety disorder. As many people I was hesitant to accept that, and accept help. I thought I was just overworked or exhausted. But I came to realize that fear was at the core of who I was and what I did.'
